The Borrowers is a children's fantasy novel by the English author Mary Norton, published by Dent in 1952. It features a family of tiny people who live secretly in the walls and floors of an English house and "borrow" from the big people in order to survive. Alternatively, The Borrowers is the series of five novels including four sequels that feature the same family after they leave "their" house.The Borrowers won the 1952 Carnegie Medal from the Library Association, recognising the year's outstanding children's book by a British subject. In the 70th anniversary celebration of the medal in 2007 it was named one of the top ten Medal-winning works,selected by a panel to compose the ballot for a public election of the all-time favourite.Harcourt, Brace and Company published it in the U.S. the next year with illustrations by Beth and Joe Krush.